snippet.textDisplay:
Don't replace deep cycle batteries. Just find the right charger, and they'll work like new (it's not your average battery). If you can't control your OCD. At least sell the used battery, they ALWAYS sell like fresh bread. They hold their value.

They don't go bad, no acid in them. Very different components than regular batteries. You can even take them to your local auto parts store. They will have the right charger and do it free. Takes about 24 hours to charge, as it's not a normal charge for a dead battery. Then after, you can use it as normal.

Even acid batteries can be rescued. Check the acid level in all the cells. Check for corrosion in the plates. If everything checks out. If needed add distilled water, enough to cover the plates. But not all the way up, needs an air gap for fumes. Then use the right charger, that can rescue batteries. Next day, you'll have a perfectly functioning battery for many years.

If they're just dead, just charge them. Batteries are not too kind to the environment. You can save money by having the right charger. It don't need to be a fancy expensive one. Just have the right setting.
